what is issue with other 2 server which i am unable to connect

The issue is SSH host key verification, not Ansible itself.

From your output:

172.31.19.177 | SUCCESS => pong

This server is working because its SSH host key was accepted and stored in:

~/.ssh/known_hosts

But for the other two servers:

172.31.19.227 | UNREACHABLE!
Failed to connect to the host via ssh: Host key verification failed.

172.31.20.209 | UNREACHABLE!
Failed to connect to the host via ssh: Host key verification failed.

This usually happens when:

The EC2 instance was terminated and recreated with the same IP.
The host key changed.
An old entry exists in ~/.ssh/known_hosts.
Verify manually

Check known_hosts:

cat ~/.ssh/known_hosts

Search for those IPs:

ssh-keygen -F 172.31.19.227
ssh-keygen -F 172.31.20.209
Remove old fingerprints
ssh-keygen -R 172.31.19.227
ssh-keygen -R 172.31.20.209

Example output:

# Host 172.31.19.227 found: line 5
/home/ec2-user/.ssh/known_hosts updated.
Test SSH
ssh ec2-user@172.31.19.227

and

ssh ec2-user@172.31.20.209

You should see:

The authenticity of host '172.31.19.227' can't be established.
Are you sure you want to continue connecting (yes/no)?

Type:

yes

This adds the new fingerprint to known_hosts.

Run Ansible again
ansible all -m ping

Expected:

172.31.19.177 | SUCCESS => pong
172.31.19.227 | SUCCESS => pong
172.31.20.209 | SUCCESS => pong
Quick enterprise workaround

Many labs use:

[defaults]
host_key_checking = False

in:

/etc/ansible/ansible.cfg

or

[ssh_connection]
ssh_args = -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no

Then Ansible automatically accepts new host keys.

Check your SSH connectivity manually first:

ssh ec2-user@172.31.19.227
ssh ec2-user@172.31.20.209

and share the output. That will tell us whether the problem is only host key verification or if there is also a key-pair, security group, or user-access issue.

